pc:TextEquiv.pc:Unicode: I Put My Trust in Thee.
Words and Music by J. H. F.
1. My Saviour and my Friend, I trust in thee a- - lone; I know thou cam'st from God, And art his on-ly
2. No dangers e'er shall harm The children of thy care, However great their fear, Thy pow'r is always
shield from ev-'ry foe, Thy hand will ever be, To guard the humblest soul, That puts its trust in thee.
4. Thy word shall never fail, Tho' earth may pass a-way; Thro' ev-'ry change thy love Will lead to perfect
my all to thee, From thee it sure-ly came; O help me ev-'ry day, To thy name.
